We’ve all heard the phrase “a brother from another mother” 

Well in this case….it’s true! 

Some 40 odd years later and he STILL remains the source of most of my hangovers!! 

Hundreds of thousands of beers….oops…I mean miles covered, countless concerts, too many songs to remember them all, a couple of pubs entered, and STILL our friendship remains life-long …HAPPY BIRTHDAY SAM!!! ❤️🥂🍾🍻🎂⭐️💥

Ok so ME. Well I did it! I got through it. Those of you who know me know me as a bit of a perfectionist especially vocally and I worried and stressed ( and coughed) my way to you losing Ottawa, Kingston & Peterbourgh along the way. Judging by all the great comments I have seen this morning I pulled it off. It’s very difficult when you know in your heart your voice can soar yet (cough cough) it’s rather limited. But that’s life. This is a pandemic of epic proportions and we just have to soldier on. 

Now YOU. What can I say guys? Words don’t truly suffice. I could NEVER have been able to do that without YOU!!! I drew my strength from you. Every ounce of it. Every ( sometimes croaky) note. You truly were my heart and soul and I THANKYOU. ❤️You were a truly INCREDIBLE INSPIRATION. 

The flask….thank you little flask. Thank you for holding that little “nippy sweetie” inside your belly. You hugged my vocal cords like a loving friend so much so …..I told “tea” to fuck off! ( it’s okay I will say,”I’m sorry” later.)
So there ya have it. WE DID IT TOGETHER! Happy Holidays guys 🥂🍾❤️ #glasstiger #alanfrewglasstiger @masseyhall #bands #liveperformance #you #me #flask

Guys by the time midnight comes along for me I will be performing with my own FREWBAND ~ so let me just wish you all the very best for #2023 ; may it bring you a profound sense of peace, happiness , health, joy and prosperity. I know those words can be very hard to come by in reality because this journey of life is tough. It can be cruel and harsh and we all feel the blunt of that at times. But what do we do? WE GET UP! WE KEEP MOVING ! WE SOLDIER ON! If it knocks us down 10 times we get up 11! SO BRING ON 2023 goodness knows your siblings ‘20, 21, & ‘22 have tried to knock the shit out of us and WE ARE STILL HERE!!! So, let’s go forward gang….. together… let’s spread kindness, love and positivity. Turn away from the naysayers and purveyors of negativity and hate .. Fuck ‘em. Let’s take on this next challenge with love in our hearts and a smile on our faces. THANK YOU on behalf of myself, my band mates, and of course on behalf of GLASS TIGER for the support you continue to give us. We love you for it and you are the sole reason we do it❤️ ok 2023 BRING IT!!🥂🍾 #glasstiger @glasstiger @enlightenedmgmt #happynewyear #lovegiveslife and #life is #love #80smusic #nosurrender #keepgoing #justdoit #instamusic

Ok! Ok! I hear you. Soooo since I have no gigs in January and only a small amount in Feb I am going to paint again. 
I will begin with a limited edition run of SOMEDAY. 

I will do a series of TEN, including the hand-written lyrics. Each painting is ONE OF A KIND. NO TWO are identical. Each will be completely unique. 

I will also make digital copies of each one so that I can turn them into NFT’s at a later date. 

Together WE will share in any revenue then NFT generates so that you have a piece of that forever. ( how fun would it be if your NFT generated what the original cost was??? Now THAT would make me happy!) Here is an example of the DON’T FORGET ME ( when I’m gone) limited edition I put out last year. 

Some of you have also asked me if I will take commissioned work on my large paintings again ( one of which I have included here) the answer is yes I am ready to tackle those again. 

If interested please just DM me here on instagram. Thanks guys ~Alan #painting #artistsoninstagram #nft #originalart #originalartwork #alanfrew #alanfrewglasstiger #drawingart #❤️

‘Round about 1993 I was recording in L.A. And had the honour of having THE @micky_dolenz sing with me and THE @mickfleetwoodofficial drum for me on my solo CD “Hold On” co-produced by my songwriting partner @johnjonesmusic I mean COME ON! does it get better than that? 
Anyway on a break Micky, Mick and yours truly step out the room and have a tea, coffee etc at the studio canteen area. Suddenly we are joined by David Crosby. 
The three of them get to chatting and reminiscing about their overlapping lives and careers and I just lean back and listen to my YOUTH being discussed right before my very eyes. Sad to hear of David’s passing today. Déjà vu  brother ….”We have all been here before.” #CSN #CSNY #dejavu #maestro #songwiter #youth #woodstock #perfomer #singer #guitarist #hippie #summeroflove #1967

When it comes to music, Canada has plenty to celebrate!

Today, we proudly announce that GLASS TIGER will be joining  with Canada’s rock royalty from the ‘70s and ‘80s entering into the distinguished ranks of Canada’s Walk of Fame: 

To celebrate the mega Induction which is the 25th Anniversary Year, "Canada's Rock of Fame" will take place at Toronto's historic Massey Hall on Thursday, September 28th. 

This unforgettable night will induct rock legends with special guests, a DJ legends reunion, surprise presenters, and live performances of beloved hits.

Tickets for Canada’s Rock of Fame go on sale Friday, July 14 at 10 a.m. ET at Ticketmaster. Stay tuned for announcements of presenters, performers, and special guests in the coming weeks.

I often get asked about tracks like HEALING HANDS and this one SO BLIND both of which are from my solo CD “HOLD ON” which I wrote and recorded in Hollywood California with my co-writer and producer @johnjonesmusic. “So Blind” was a bonafide number one hit it Canada and Hold On remains one of my proudest creative endveavors to date.  Song for song I believe it stands the test of time. A labour of love created over a period of a year I had the opportunity to work with some of the finest musicians in the world; Steve Ferrone, Jim Cregan , Micky Dolenz, John Jones, Robin Le Mesurier and Mick Fleetwood to name but a few. Definitely Hold On is one of the highlights of my long career and I look back on it fondly. When I look at the photos from “Changes, Like a seed to a flower/ Like a boy to a man ~ I realize just how fast it has all gone by. A thousand years ago was indeed just yesterday. Live for the moment my friends. Live for the moment.❤️ #alanfrew #holdon #soblind #solo #career #instamusic #instasongs #losangeles #studio #music

Oh P.E.I. I am sorry…I gave  it my best shot by still travelling here but I cannot win this particular battle. My throat is swollen and sore and my voice is gone😰 Those who know me, KNOW how this kills me. The pressure of the singer is unbearable at times because everything rests on those two tiny cords within the throat and mine are not doing well today. Well I cannot believe it, but that’s it for summer gigs my friends. Wow! Again, where does this time go? As many of you know, the last month or more has been extremely difficult on me with whatever this shit is that got me. As a vocalist , it’s been one of the toughest times of my career. However, we all got through it together and now I can rest these weary vocal cords. We still have some dates left to do including, Cancun, Edmonton, Calgary, Kelowna, Vancouver & Victoria, November & December. Thank you all for your summer support, most recently you, New Westminster, B.C., we had a fabulous time. PEI again, our apologies for cancelling on you. Had I had “any” voice left at all I would have given it my all to sing for you. We will see you again, soon enough. 
And so we head into fall of 2023 with gratitude for all of your love and support. I have several interesting solo projects I am working on and will share them with you soon. Happy last few days of summer guys ❤️~Alan #summer #summertime #summervibes #singing #performing #glasstiger #alanfrewglasstiger #gigs #touring #cancun #edmonton #calgary #kelowna #vancouver # Victoria #80smusic #insta80s #instamusic

For what is worth this is the “only” photo I have of me as a child. There was one solo one that was borrowed by “MuchMusic” years ago but I never got it back. The ladies in this photo are teachers of the kindergarten I attended. I come from a generation that; 

Walked to school and then walked back.

A generation that did their homework alone to get out asap to play in the street.

A generation that spent all their free time in the streets with their Friends.

A generation that played hide and seek when dark.

A generation that made mud cakes, played with a stick, stones or a ball.

A generation that collected sports cards, stamps, and coins.

A generation who ran home from school because either ; The Monkees, The Flintstones, Bewitched, I Dream Of Jeannie or Thunderbirds were on TV. 

A generation that found, collected. washed & returned empty coke bottles to the local grocery store for 5 cents each , then bought a Mountain Dew and candy bar with the money. 

A generation that made paper toys with their bare hands.

A generation who bought vinyl albums to play on record players and read every word of the liner notes .

A generation that collected photos and albums of clippings of their life experiences as a Kid.

A generation that played board games and cards on rainy days.

A generation whose TV went off at midnight after playing the National Anthem.

A generation that had parents who were there for them AFTER coming in from the street and the dark.

A generation that laughed under the covers in bed so parents didn't know we were still awake.

A generation that is passing and unfortunately it will never return no matter how hard we try.

I loved Growing up when I did. it was the best of times. And although I would love to live forever, I am not jealous of the generations who follow me . #child #chilhood #childlhoodmemories #boy #boyhood_photos #life #instalife #kid #growingup #growingold #ilovelife #thisisyourlife #alanfrew #alanfrewglasstiger #mychildhood #mygeneration

Well tonight’s the night. 37 years of being a recording act and about 45 years of singing for a band and it’s an honour to be inducted into Canada’s Walk Of Fame. As for the other artists congrat’s to all its gonna be like a “family gathering” with all of you @glasstiger @glasstigerkeys @enlightenedmgmt @feldmanagency @livenationon  #walkoffame #canada #dontforgetmewhenimgone #alanfrewglasstiger #alanfrew

“Like a seed to a flower, Like a boy to man.”

What a night! @cwofame @glasstiger had a blast performing and joining all of our fellow inductees on the @masseyhall stage. 

One personal faux pas on my part……During my “thank you’s” I got a little distracted when telling a story of the writing of SOMEDAY & DON’T FORGET ME ( when I’m gone) and in doing so, it slipped my mind to thank someone who was SO IMPORTANT to the career of @glasstiger and for the rest of the evening it drove me crazy that I had omitted to mention him. 

His name was Deane Cameron and as the head of A&R for Capitol records he was directly responsible, along with his second-in-command , Tim Trombley, in signing Glass Tiger to our international record deal, changing our lives forever. 

Deane later went on to become the President of Capitol, signing me again, as a solo artist for my two CD’S ; HOLD ON & WONDERLAND. 

More recently he was appointed President of the Massey Hall group and his dream project became it’s beautiful renovation. 

The last time I was with him we had lunch then donned our “hard hats” for a tour of the ongoing changes being made to the “Grand Dame” of Canadian Theatres. He beamed as he walked me through it telling me of “what was to come.”

Sadly, Deane died suddenly never seeing his dream through to completion. 

Today, within the newly renovated building, there is a beautiful recording studio aptly named after Deane. 

Although “gutted”, I was honoured to eulogize him at his funeral and it saddened me greatly to think that just years before, I had been asked to be part of his induction into the Hall Of Fame. 

In 2015 when I suffered a stroke I will never forget him standing at my front door with a box of chocolates in his hand and he stayed to visit with me for a short while. 

Kind, caring, forthright, fiercely Canadian and a legend within our industry, ladies and gentleman I hereby thank Deane Cameron. Love you pal and you are sooooooo missed by our industry, your colleagues and friends and of course your loved ones. ~Alan ❤️

Last week, our hearts were filled with gratitude as we stood alongside iconic Canadian Rock artists at the "Rock of Fame" ceremony at Massey Hall. ⭐ It's an incredible honour to be inducted into Canada's Walk of Fame, and it wouldn't have been possible without all of YOU!

To our fans, families, friends, and collaborators, thank you for being on this incredible journey with us. 🙏 Your unwavering support and love for our music has fuelled our passion and creativity throughout the years. 

This milestone is not just ours, but it belongs to every single one of you who has been a part of the Glass Tiger family over the years. ❤️

Here's to the music that brings us together and the memories we've created. Cheers to a legendary night we will never forget!

With heartfelt thanks,

Glass Tiger

10 Things I did in 2023 1) Announced my 80s>90s Rewind  concert in Toronto Feb 17th 2024 2) Got Inducted into Canada’s Walk Of Fame 3)Created ( by popular demand) a new 2024 Calendar. 4) Performed with GT in Mexico 5) Fell in love with a dog hugging a Union Flag chewy bone toy 6) Saw an AI photo of my dad, my sis, and me when I was about knee-high to a grasshopper 7) Hung out with my brothers 8) Continued to sing my ass off. 9) Held a band meeting about which pub to go to after the band meeting 10) Continued to not let life get me down.

Ten more things I did in 2023; 1) Flew an awful lot 2) wore my funky cardigan 3) Was honoured that Glass Tiger was our beloved @marilyndenis ‘s final guests of her final show. 4) had a cup of tea. 5) Realized how much “baby Federico” came into the world looking like Sir Winston. 6) Realized my being on “coke” wasn’t good for me. 7) Sang my ass off. 8) Took in all of Canada’s beauty, yet again. 9) Bought a funky T-shirt 10) Realized that I actually have the best seat in the house, looking out at all of you.

“Ten More Things” I did in 2023 ; 1) I looked up a tree. 2) Mourned the loss of a true Canadian Legend. 3) Had a Guinness with a handsome Italian pal, who hates Guinness, but who was told if he didn’t drink it, I would tell his mamma that he stole her GT jacket. 4) Decided that “This Island Earth, is indeed, my favourite Glass Tiger song. 5) Stayed in touch with friends I love to laugh with. 6) Made the bus, “just in time!” 7) Sang my ass off. 8) Enjoyed a beautiful Tuscan sunset. 9) Painted a different view of our beloved, “Maple Leaf.” 10) Simply put, ……I “reminisced.”

Ten more things I did in 2023. 1) Polished my gift from Rod Stewart. When Rod found out that I was actually the first vocalist to sing live at “The Skydome” he handed me his award, signed to me. 2) Saw this wonderful wacky photo of members of my 80>90Rewind audience dressed in “full regalia!” 3) Introduced an “Italian” to three Scottish pals of mine 4) Sang my ass off. 5) Caught the morning sunrise and the beauty of “the prairies” yet again. 6) Found this old photo of me sleeping having scoured every inch of my latest vinyl! Just looking at it here I can tell what album it is. 7) Did a photoshoot with my brothers courtesy of great photographer David Leyes 8) Bought a baseball cap 9) In my 80>90Rewind set list I LOVE doing RELAX by Frankie Goes To Hollywood 10) Simply put…I reminisced . #rodstewart #80s #90s #music #concerts #hits #songs #praries #baseball

Ten more things I did in 2023; 1) Reminisced about meeting Paul McCartney. It’s not often yours truly is speechless but that came close. 2) Listened to my CD 80290Rewind. I realize the “upgrade” my solo band has experienced since this was released . The new set list is “off the charts” killer. 3) Had a few drinks/ filled out a survey 4) Polished my award from the legendary Joe Cocker for the hit song FIRE IT UP 5) Found a “bobblehead” in amongst my Junos 6) Told the story of a special duet moment. This was my first gig following my stroke and the amazing Nelly Furtado popped down to support me 7) Reminded myself that you are NEVER out of the fight!! 8) had a chuckle at that “lad” 9) Was pissed when I returned to find the roof had blown off my house. 10) Wrote a story about a “record deal.” #paulmccartney #thebeatles #alcohol #nellyfurtado #alanfrew #alanfrewglasstiger #joecocker #recorddeal #rome #roma #collesseum #junoawards #songs #hits #passion #instamusic
